<subSubSection id="E3EA1CE3FF987C08FF2FFD836B69FDAC" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="AB4F4F68FF987C08FF2FFD836B69FDAC" blockId="4.[151,1437,153,791]" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis id="9984937AFF987C08FF2FFD836B0FFDF0" bold="true" box="[199,334,549,575]" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">Etymology.</emphasis>
This new species name, a noun, is the name of the group of indigenous “ 
<emphasis id="9984937AFF987C08FB9DFD836EEAFDF0" box="[1141,1195,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">Adi”</emphasis>
people inhabiting the 
<typeStatus id="744BF1CAFF987C08FF7FFDEF6A86FDAC" box="[151,199,585,611]" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E3EA1CE3FF987C08FF2FFDCB6915FCD8" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="AB4F4F68FF987C08FF2FFDCB6915FCD8" blockId="4.[151,1437,153,791]" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis id="9984937AFF987C08FF2FFDCB6B7AFD48" bold="true" box="[199,315,621,647]" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="6CF034EBFF987C08FEACFDCB6BB7FD48" authority="Singaravel &amp; Singaravel, 2020" authorityName="Singaravel &amp; Singaravel" authorityYear="2020" box="[324,502,621,647]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="9984937AFF987C08FEACFDCB6BB7FD48" box="[324,502,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">Hishimonus adi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="82B72E01FF987C08FE17FDCB6816FD48" box="[511,599,621,647]" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
closely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="6CF034EBFF987C08FCD8FDC86E59FD47" authority="(Distant)" baseAuthorityName="Distant" box="[816,1048,621,648]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phycitis">
<emphasis id="9984937AFF987C08FCD8FDC869EAFD48" box="[816,939,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">H. phycitis</emphasis>
(Distant)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="6CF034EBFF987C08FBBAFDC86A9EFD64" authority="Dai, Fletcher &amp; Zhang" authorityName="Dai, Fletcher &amp; Zhang" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diffractus">
<emphasis id="9984937AFF987C08FBBAFDC86EA0FD48" box="[1106,1249,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">H. diffractus</emphasis>
Dai, Fletcher &amp; Zhang
</taxonomicName>
but differs in having the aedeagal shaft: with lobe like median process in lateral view which is absent (in 
<taxonomicName id="6CF034EBFF987C08FA69FD346AAFFD00" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phycitis">
<emphasis id="9984937AFF987C08FA69FD346AAFFD00" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">H. phycitis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or sharp thorn like on inner margin (in 
<taxonomicName id="6CF034EBFF987C08FD42FD106977FD00" box="[682,822,693,719]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diffractus">
<emphasis id="9984937AFF987C08FD42FD106977FD00" box="[682,822,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">H. diffractus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), with subapical lateral lamellate expansion rather than apical lamellation (in 
<taxonomicName id="6CF034EBFF987C08FE79FD7C684DFD3C" box="[401,524,729,755]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phycitis">
<emphasis id="9984937AFF987C08FE79FD7C684DFD3C" box="[401,524,729,755]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">H. phycitis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or no lamellation (in 
<taxonomicName id="6CF034EBFF987C08FCFAFD7C69E0FD3C" box="[786,929,729,755]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diffractus">
<emphasis id="9984937AFF987C08FCFAFD7C69E0FD3C" box="[786,929,729,755]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">H. diffractus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and with apical gonopore opening whereas opens subapically on posterior surface in the later two species.
</paragraph>
